expand /ɪkˈspænd/

(expanding,expanded,expands) 

1. V-T/V-I If something expands or is expanded , it becomes larger. 扩大; 膨胀 

例： Engineers noticed that the pipes were not expanding as expected. 工程师们注意到管子并未像预期的那样膨胀。 

例： We have to expand the size of the image. 我们不得不扩大图像的尺寸。 

2. V-T/V-I If something such as a business, organization, or service expands , or if you expand it, it becomes bigger and includes more people, goods, or activities. 使…发展; 发展 [商业] 

例： The popular ceramics industry expanded toward the middle of the 19th century. 大众陶瓷业在19世纪中叶得到了发展。

